\ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\b\f0\fs19 Activate Blindly:}{\f0\fs20 
 Some magic items are activated by special words, thoughts, or actions. You can activate such items as if you were using the activation word, thought, or action even if you\rquote re not, and even if you don\rquote 
t know it. You do have to use something equivalent. You have to speak, wave the item around, or otherwise attempt to get it to activate. You get a +2 bonus on the check if you\rquote ve activated the item at least once in the past.
\par If you fail the check by 10 or more, you suffer a mishap. A mishap means that magical energy is released, but it doesn\rquote 
t do what you wanted it to. The GM determines the result of a mishap. The default mishaps are that the item affects the wrong target or that uncontrolled magical energy deals 2d6 points of damage to you. This mishap is in a
ddition to the chance for a mishap normally associated with casting a spell from a scroll when the spell\rquote s caster level is higher than your level in this class.
\par }{\b\f0\fs19 Decipher a Written Spell:}{\f0\fs20  This works like the same use of the Spellcraft skill (see the Mage Advanced Class), except that the DC is 5 points higher. Deciphering a written spell takes 1 minute of concentration.
\par }{\b\f0\fs19\expnd-1\expndtw-5 Emulate Class Feature:}{\f0\fs20\expnd-1\expndtw-5  Sometimes you need a class }{\f0\fs20 feature to activate a magic item. Your effective level in the emulated class equals your check result minus 20.
\par This skill use doesn\rquote t allow you to use the class feature of another class. It just lets you activate items as if you had the class feature.
\par If the class whose feature you are emulating has an allegiance requirement, you must meet it. This may require a separate check to emulate allegiance (see below).
\par }{\b\f0\fs19 Emulate Ability Score:}{\b\f0\fs20\expnd-1\expndtw-5  }{\f0\fs20\expnd-1\expndtw-5 To cast a spell from a scroll, you need a high ability score in the appro
priate ability (Intelligence for arcane spells, Wisdom for divine spells). Your effective ability score (appropriate to the class you\rquote 
re emulating when you try to cast a spell from a scroll) equals your check result minus 15. If you already have a high enough score in the ability, you don\rquote t need to make this check.
\par }{\b\f0\fs19 Emulate Allegiance:}{\f0\fs20  Some magic items have positive or negative effects based on your allegiance. You can use these items as if you were of an allegiance of your choice. You can only emulate one allegiance at a time.
\par }{\b\f0\fs19 Use a Scroll: }{\f0\fs20 
Normally, to cast a spell from a scroll, you must belong to a class that has access to the arcane or divine spell inscribed therein. This use of the skill allows you to use a scroll as if you were of the appropriate spell
casting class. The DC equals 20 + the caster level of the spell you are trying to cast from the scroll. To cast a spell from a scroll, you must first decipher it.
\par In addition, casting a spell from a scroll requires a minimum score of 10 + the spell\rquote s level in the appropriate ability. If you don\rquote t have a sufficiently high score, you must emulate the ability score with a separate check (see above).

\par }{\b\f0\fs19 Use a Wand:}{\b\f0\fs20  }{\f0\fs20 Normally, to use a wand you must belong to a class that has access to the arcane or divine spell ens
orcelled therein. This use of the skill allows you to use a wand as if you were of the appropriate spellcasting class.
\par }{\b\f0\fs19 Try Again?:}{\b\f0\fs20  }{\f0\fs20 Yes, but if you ever roll a natural 1 while attempting to activate an item and you fail the check, then you can\rquote t try to activate that item again for 24 hours.
\par }{\b\f0\fs19 Special:}{\f0\fs20  You can\rquote t take 10 or take 20 with this skill. Magic is too unpredictable to make the use of this skill reliable.
\par }\pard\plain \s4\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel3\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f5\fs30\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\f0\fs20 
