\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Hit Dice:}{\f0\fs20  Treat as the Mage\rquote s character level (for effects related to Hit Dice). Use the familiar\rquote s normal total if it is higher.
\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Hit Points:}{\f0\fs20  One-half the Mage\rquote s total, rounded down. 
\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Action Points:}{\f0\fs20  A familiar cannot gain or spend action points, and a Mage cannot spend an action point through his familiar.
\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Attacks:}{\f0\fs20  Use the Mage\rquote s base attack bonus. Use the familiar\rquote s Dexterity modifier or Strength modifier, whichever is greater, to determine the familiar\rquote 
s melee attack bonus with unarmed attacks. Damage equals that of a normal creature of its type.
\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Saving Throws:}{\f0\fs20  The familiar uses the Mage\rquote s base saving throw bonuses if they\rquote re better than the familiar\rquote s. The familiar uses its own ability modifiers to save
s, and does not enjoy other bonuses that the Mage may have (such as from feats).
\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Skills:}{\f0\fs20  For each skill, use either the normal skill ranks for a creature of its type or the Mage\rquote s skill ranks, whichever is better. In either case, the familiar uses its own ability modifiers. Regardless of a familiar
\rquote s total skill modifiers, some skills may remain beyond the ability of the familiar to perform (such as Craft, for instance). 
\par }{\b\f0\fs20 Familiar Special Abilities: }{\f0\fs20 Familiars have special abilities, or impart abilities to their Mages, depending on the level of the Mage.
\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Natural Armor (Ex): }{\f0\fs20 This number represents a bonus to the familiar\rquote s existing natural armor bonus to Defense. Add the given value directly to the familiar\rquote s Defense. It represents a familiar\rquote s preternatural t
oughness.
\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Familiar\rquote s Intelligence (Ex):}{\f0\fs20  The familiar\rquote s Intelligence score. (Normal creatures of its type have a much lower Intelligence score.)
\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Alertness (Ex):}{\f0\fs20  The presence of a familiar sharpens its master\rquote s senses. While the familiar is within 5 feet, the Mage gains the Alertness feat.
\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Share Spells (Su):}{\f0\fs20  At the Mage\rquote s option, he may have any spell he casts on himself also affect his familiar. The familiar must be within 5 feet at the time. If the spell has a duration other than instantaneous, the spell st
ops affecting the familiar if the creature moves farther than 5 feet away. The spell\rquote 
s effect is not restored even if the familiar returns to the Mage before the duration would otherwise have ended. Additionally, the Mage may cast a spell with a target of \'93You\'94
 on his familiar (as a touch range spell) instead of on himself. The Mage and the familiar can share spells even if the spells normally do not affect creatures of the familiar\rquote s type (magical beast).
\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Empathic Link (Su):}{\f0\fs20  The Mage has an empathic link with the familiar out to a distance of up to 1 mile. The Mage can\rquote t see through the familiar\rquote 
s eyes, but the two of them can communicate telepathically. Note that the relatively low Intelligence of a low-level Mage\rquote s familiar limits what it is able to commu
nicate or understand, and even intelligent familiars see the world differently from humans.
\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Touch (Su):}{\f0\fs20  The familiar of a Mage who is 3rd level or higher can deliver touch spells for him. When the mage casts a touch spell, he can designate his familiar as the \'93toucher.\'94
 (The Mage and the familiar have to be in contact at the time of casting.) The familiar can then deliver the touch spell just as the Mage could. As normal, if the Mage casts another spell, the touch spell dissipates.
\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Improved Evasion (Ex):}{\f0\fs20  If
 a familiar is subjected to an attack that normally allows a Reflex saving throw for half damage, the familiar takes no damage if it makes a successful saving throw and half damage even if the saving throw fails.
\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Speak with Familiar/Speak with Master (Ex):}{\f0\fs20  A Mage of 5th level or higher and his familiar can communicate verbally as if they were using a common language. Other creatures do not understand the communication without magical help.

\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Speak with Animals of Its Type (Ex):}{\f0\fs20  The familiar of a Mage of 7th l
evel or higher can communicate with animals of approximately the same type as itself: bats and rats with rodents, cats with felines, ferrets with creatures of the family Mustelidae (weasels, minks, polecats, ermines, skunks, wolverines, and badgers), hawk
s and owls with birds, snakes with reptiles, toads with amphibians. The communication is limited by the Intelligence of the conversing creatures.
\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Spell Resistance (Ex): }{\f0\fs20 The familiar of a Mage of 9th level or higher gains spell resistance equal to the Mage\rquote s level + 5.
