k. Creatures that would be turned are rebuked instead, and those that would be destroyed are commanded.
\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Rebuked: }{\f0\fs20 A rebuked creature cowers as if in awe (can take no actions, \endash 2 penalty to Defense) for 10 rounds.
\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Commanded: }{\f0\fs20 A commanded creature falls under the mental control of the Acolyte. The Acolyte can give mental orders to a commanded creature as an attack action. The Acolyte can command any number of creatures whose total Hit Dice don
\rquote t exceed her Acolyte level. She may voluntarily relinquish command in order to establish command on different creatures.
\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Dispel Turning: }{\f0\fs20 An evil Acolyte may dispel the turning effect of a good Acolyte. To do so, the evil Acolyte makes a turning check as if attempting to rebuke. If the turning check result is equal to or gr
eater than the turning check result that the good Acolyte scored when turning them, then the creatures are no longer turned. The evil Acolyte rolls turning damage to see how many Hit Dice worth of creatures she can affect in this way.
\par }{\i\f0\fs20 Bolster Undead:}{\f0\fs20  An evil Acolyte may bolster creatures against turning effects in advance. She makes a turning check as if attempting to rebuke them, but the Hit Dice result becomes the creatures\rquote 
 effective Hit Dice as far as turning is concerned (provided the result is higher than the creatures\rquote  normal Hit Dice). This bolstering lasts for 10 rounds.
\par }\pard\plain \s3\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel2\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\up3\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\up0 Bonus Feats
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f5\fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\fs20 
At 3rd, 6th, and 9th level, the Acolyte gets a bonus feat. The bonus feat must be selected from the following list, and the Acolyte must meet all the prerequisites of the feat to select it.
\par Animal Affinity, Archaic Weapons Proficiency, Armor Proficiency (light), Attentive, Combat Expertise, Educated, Frightful Presence, Iron Will, Medical Expert, Studious, Trustworthy.
\par }\pard\plain \s3\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel2\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\up3\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\up0 Spontaneous Casting
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f5\fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\fs20 An Acolyte of 4th level or higher can channel stored energy into spells she has not prepared ahead of time. The Acolyte 
\'93loses\'94 a prepared spell to cast another spell of the same level or lower.
\par An Acolyte with a good allegiance can spontaneously cast cure spells (spells with \'93cure\'94 in their name). An Acolyte with an evil allegiance can spontaneously convert prepared spells into inflict spells (spells with \'93inflict\'94 in their name).

\par }\pard\plain \s3\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel2\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\up3\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\up0 Combat Casting
