At 8th level, the Acolyte gains the supernatural ability to affect outsiders. This ability works just like turning undead and magical beasts, except the creature type is outsider. Outsiders, unlike undead creatures, can\rquote t be dest
royed or commanded. All other rules pertaining to turning apply. The number of times per day the Acolyte can make a turning attempt (3 + Cha modifier) does not increase.
\par }{\b\f0\fs20 Maximize Spell
\par }{\f0\fs20 At 10th level, an Acolyte learns to cast some of her spells to maximum 
effect. All variable, numeric effects of a maximized spell automatically achieve their maximum values. A maximized spell deals the most possible points of damage, affects the maximum number of targets, and so forth, as appropriate. Saving throws and oppos
ed checks are not affected. Spells without random variables are not affected. 
\par When a maximized spell is prepared, it is treated as a spell of three levels higher than the spell\rquote s actual level.
\par }}